Currently support credit/debit cards. After adding a card, you’ll see a temporary $10 authorization on your card, which will be removed if your ad cost is less than $10 after 7 days.
explain hpw is it works

When you add a credit or debit card to your NewsBreak account, a temporary $10 authorization fee is placed on your card. This is a standard procedure to verify the card's validity. If you run ads and your ad cost is less than $10 within 7 days, this amount will be applied towards your advertising budget. If you don't run any ads or if the ad cost doesn't reach $10, the authorization will be removed after 7 days, and the funds will be released back to your card.
